gomodel:SYNGO_485  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Supplemental table S1 contains 698 synaptic proteins identified in three different experimental approaches: isolated PSD preparation, MAGUK-associated signalling complexes (MASC) and AMPA receptor complexes (ARCs). VCP was found in the isolated PSD fraction (which may contain also presynaptic components). SynGO ID 483).\n\n16/5/2017 Pim\n- Because PSD fraction does also contain some pre-synaptic proteins, the Gundelfinger lab chose the more broad term \"synapse\".. Experimental description: Here we present a large-scale proteomic analysis of the\npostsynaptic proteome (PSP) of mouse brain. p.17" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_485" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

